# ============================================================
# Supplementary analysis script
# GBM DSP proteomic and transcriptomic unsupervised heatmaps
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Purpose:
#   (1) Import NanoString GeoMx DSP proteomic data from DCC/PKC files,
#       perform QC, normalize counts, curate sample annotations, rank
#       proteins by coefficient of variation (CV), and generate
#       unsupervised heatmaps for the top 20%, 10%, and 5% most variable
#       proteins.
#   (2) Generate a transcriptomic unsupervised heatmap from a prepared
#       RNA ExpressionSet-like object using matched annotation logic and
#       dynamic figure sizing.
#
# Notes:
#   1. Update all paths in the CONFIGURATION section before running.
#   2. The transcriptomic section assumes that an object named
#      `target_demoData` has already been created upstream and contains
#      a log-transformed assay named `log_q`.
#   3. This script is formatted for supplemental reproducibility and may
#      be adapted further for repository release.
# ============================================================

